Add a comprehensive health-check and diagnostics system. Create `src/health.js` with the following: 1) `health.check()` - runs all registered checks and returns `{ status: 'ok'|'degraded'|'failing', checks: [...] }` where each check entry has `{ name, status, message, durationMs }`. 2) `health.register(name, fn)` - register a named async check function that returns `{ ok: boolean, message: string }`. 3) Built-in checks already registered: (a) 'memory' - checks heap usage is below 90%, (b) 'eventLoop' - measures event loop lag and fails if > 100ms, (c) 'config' - validates the config module's required keys are present. 4) `health.summary()` - returns a one-line human-readable string like 'All 3 checks passing' or '1/3 checks failing'. 5) `health.toJSON()` - returns the full diagnostic report as JSON including Node.js version, uptime, and memory stats. 6) Add an HTTP health endpoint: create `src/healthServer.js` that starts a lightweight HTTP server (using only Node's built-in `http` module) on a configurable port (default 9090) that responds to GET /health with the JSON report and appropriate status codes (200 for ok, 207 for degraded, 503 for failing). 7) Write tests in `tests/health.test.js`. 8) Export both modules from `src/index.js`. 9) Add a `forever health` CLI subcommand in `bin/forever.js` that runs the health checks and prints a formatted report.